Reinilde was born in a place called Condacum, now identified with the Cond√©-sur-l'escaut or Kontich, and was the daughter of the duke of Lotaringia Vitgero and saint Amalberga. The brother sant Emeberto was a priest in the diocese of Cambrai, and his biography mentions it as a sister of st Gudula.His hagiography, written between 1048 and 1051 in the Abbey of Lobbes,Vita Reineldis, Acta Sanctorum, Julii, IV, 173-178. register for this event by speaking of his visit to Jerusalem.Back home he devoted himself to a life of works of charity in Saintes. Died beheaded by the Huns in Saintes with the deacon Grimoald and his servant
CultoSanta Reinilde is venerated especially in Saintes, the French city of which he is the patron saint. Some sources claim that the city owes its name to the martyrdom of Reinilde.
The parish church of Saintes is dedicated to santa Reinilde since the middle ages and has preserved the relics of the saint.
The patronage of the holy Reinilde for the affections of the eye disease is due to the association with a source of water in Saintes known as "the well of santa Reinilde", the water that is believed cirasse eye disease.
